  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth\nVersion: 1.5.0-unstable\nProtocol Versions: [63 62 61]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.6.1\nOS: linux\nGOPATH=\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go-1.6\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nmyaddress = server.eth_accounts()[0]\nprint server.eth_getBalance([myaddress, \"latest\"])\n#### Actual behaviour\n\n**jsonrpclib.jsonrpc.ProtocolError: (-32602, u'Invalid address length, expected 40 got 56 bytes')**\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nI try to call the eth_getBalance method from python.\n\nimport jsonrpclib\nserver = jsonrpclib.Server('http://<ip>:8545')\nprint \"clientVersion: %s\" % server.web3_clientVersion()\n**myaddress = server.eth_accounts()[0]**\nprint \"My address: %s\" % myaddress\nprint \"Unlock account: %s\" % server.personal_unlockAccount(myaddress,\"GEHEIM\", 60)\nprint \"Lock account: %s\" % server.personal_lockAccount(myaddress)\n\nresults in:\nclientVersion: Geth/v1.5.0-unstable/linux/go1.6.1\nMy address: 0x693b53714fffefdccb0ac6af2a20660892fadfca\nUnlock account: True\nLock account: True\n\nGetting the address and using this address for unlocking and locking works, but when I try to use getBalance I get this error:\n\n**print server.eth_getBalance([myaddress, \"latest\"])**\n\n**jsonrpclib.jsonrpc.ProtocolError: (-32602, u'Invalid address length, expected 40 got 56 bytes')**\n\nNot sure if I made an error here. I tried to find examples but is seem that is the right way to call the RPC function.\n",
